#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This module consists of three tabs with configure options how to display web "
"pages."
msgstr ""
"Ta modul je sestavljen iz treh zavihkov z možnostmi konfiguracije, kako "
"prikazati spletne strani."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "General"
msgstr "Splošno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The check box labeled <guilabel>Automatically load images</guilabel> allows "
"you to control whether images on web pages are loaded by default. Unless you "
"have a very slow connection, you will probably want to leave this option "
"selected, as there are many web pages that are difficult to use without "
"images. If you don’t select the option to automatically load images, you can "
"still view the text on the page, and then load the images if you need them."
msgstr ""
"Potrditveno polje <guilabel>Samodejno naloži slike</guilabel> vam omogoča "
"nadzor nad tem, ali se privzeto nalagajo slike na spletnih straneh. Razen če "
"imate zelo počasno povezavo, boste to možnost verjetno želeli pustiti "
"izbrano, saj je veliko spletnih strani, ki jih je težko uporabljati brez "
"slik. Če ne izberete možnosti za samodejno nalaganje slik, si lahko še vedno "
"ogledate besedilo na strani in nato naložite slike, če jih potrebujete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <guilabel>Draw frame around not completely loaded images</guilabel> is "
"checked, &konqueror; will draw a frame as a placeholder around images "
"embedded in a web page that are not yet fully loaded. You will probably want "
"to check this box to enhance your browsing experience, especially if have a "
"slow network connection."
msgstr ""
"Če je označeno <guilabel>Nariši okvir okoli nepopolno naloženih slik</"
"guilabel>, &konqueror; bo narisal okvir kot ogrado okoli slik, vdelanih v "
"spletno stran, ki še niso v celoti naložene. Verjetno boste želeli potrditi "
"to polje, da izboljšate svojo izkušnjo brskanja, še posebej, če imate "
"počasno omrežno povezavo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many web pages use animated gif images, and these can be very annoying, and "
"in some cases, quite a drain on your system resources. The "
"<guilabel>Animations</guilabel> option lets you choose when animations are "
"enabled. The default is enabled, but you can set this to disabled, or to run "
"the animation only once, even if the file itself contains instructions that "
"the animation should run more times, or continuously."
msgstr ""
"Številne spletne strani uporabljajo animirane slike gif, ki so lahko zelo "
"moteče in v nekaterih primerih precej porabljajo sistemske vire. Možnost "
"<guilabel>Animacije</guilabel> vam omogoča, da izberete, kdaj so animacije "
"omogočene. Privzeto je omogočeno, vendar lahko to nastavite na onemogočeno "
"ali pa zaženete animacijo samo enkrat, tudi če sama datoteka vsebuje "
"navodila, da se mora animacija izvajati večkrat ali neprekinjeno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The next setting is <guilabel>Underline links:</guilabel>. You can choose to "
"underline links <guilabel>Enabled</guilabel>. If this option is selected, "
"any text on web pages that acts as a link will be shown in an underlined "
"font. While many web pages do use color to distinguish text that acts as a "
"link, underlining makes it very easy to spot links."
msgstr ""
"Naslednja nastavitev je <guilabel>Podčrtane povezave:</guilabel>. Povezave "
"lahko podčrtate <guilabel>Omogočeno</guilabel>. Če izberete to možnost, bo "
"vsako besedilo na spletnih straneh, ki deluje kot povezava, prikazano s "
"podčrtano pisavo. Medtem ko številne spletne strani uporabljajo barvo za "
"razlikovanje besedila, ki deluje kot povezava, podčrtavanje olajša "
"odkrivanje povezav."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you don’t like underlined links, you can choose <guilabel>Disabled</"
"guilabel>, so that no links are underlined. Or you can choose a middle "
"ground, <guilabel>Only on Hover</guilabel>, so that links are underlined "
"when the mouse cursor is resting over them, and not underlined the rest of "
"the time."
msgstr ""
"Če vam niso všeč podčrtane povezave, lahko izberete <guilabel>Onemogočeno</"
"guilabel>, tako da nobena povezava ne bo podčrtana. Lahko pa izberete "
"srednjo pot, <guilabel>Samo pri lebdenju</guilabel>, tako da so povezave "
"podčrtane, ko miškin kazalec stoji nad njimi, preostali čas pa niso "
"podčrtane."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "The site’s CSS definitions can override this value."
msgstr "Definicije CSS spletnega mesta lahko preglasijo to vrednost."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Smooth scrolling</guilabel> determines whether &konqueror; should "
"use smooth steps to scroll &HTML; pages, or whole steps:"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Gladko drsenje</guilabel> določa, ali &konqueror; mora uporabljati "
"gladke korake za pomikanje po &HTML; strani ali celi koraki:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Always</guilabel>: Always use smooth steps when scrolling."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Vedno</guilabel>: Pri drsenju vedno uporabljajte gladke korake."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Never</guilabel>: Never use smooth scrolling, scroll with whole "
"steps instead."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Nikoli</guilabel>: nikoli ne uporabljajte gladkega drsenja, raje "
"se drsite s celimi koraki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>When Efficient</guilabel>: Only use smooth scrolling on pages "
"where it can be achieved with moderate usage of system resources."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Ko je učinkovito</guilabel>: Gladko drsenje uporabljajte samo na "
"straneh, kjer je to mogoče doseči z zmerno uporabo sistemskih virov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fonts"
msgstr "Pisave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Under this tab, you can select various options related to the use of fonts. "
"Although the shapes and sizes of fonts are often part of the design of a web "
"page, you can select some default settings for &konqueror; to use."
msgstr ""
"Pod tem jezičkom lahko izbirate različne možnosti v zvezi z uporabo pisav. "
"Čeprav sta oblika in velikost pisave pogosto del oblikovanja spletne strani, "
"lahko izberete nekaj privzetih nastavitev, da jih bo &konqueror; uporabil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first thing you can set here is the font size. There are two settings "
"which work together to allow you a comfortable browsing experience."
msgstr ""
"Prva stvar, ki jo lahko tu nastavite, je velikost pisave. To sta dve "
"nastavitvi, ki skupaj delujeta tako, da vam olajšata udobno brskanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Firstly, you can set a <guilabel>Minimum font size</guilabel>. This means, "
"even if the font size is set specifically in the page you are viewing, "
"&konqueror; will ignore that instruction and never show smaller fonts than "
"you set here."
msgstr ""
"Najprej lahko nastavite <guilabel>Najmanjšo velikost pisave</guilabel>. To "
"pomeni, da tudi če je velikost pisave določena na strani, ki si jo "
"ogledujete, &konqueror; bo prezrl to navodilo in nikoli ne bo prikazal "
"manjših pisav, kot ste jih nastavili tukaj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next you can set a <guilabel>Medium font size</guilabel>. This is not only "
"the default size of text, used when the page does not specify sizes, but it "
"is also used as the base size that relative font sizes are calculated "
"against. That is, the &HTML; instruction <quote>smaller</quote>, it means "
"smaller than the size you set for this option."
msgstr ""
"Nato lahko nastavite <guilabel>Srednjo velikost pisave</guilabel>. To ni "
"samo privzeta velikost besedila, ki se uporablja, ko stran ne določa "
"velikosti, ampak se uporablja tudi kot osnovna velikost, na podlagi katere "
"se izračunajo relativne velikosti pisave. To je &HTML; navodilo "
"<quote>manjše</quote>, pomeni manjše od velikosti, ki ste jo nastavili za to "
"možnost."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For either option, you can select the exact font size in points by using the "
"up/down spin control (or just typing) next to the option label."
msgstr ""
"Za obe izbiri lahko izberete točno velikost pisave v pikah tako, da "
"uporabite gumba za gor/dol (ali pa jo napišete) poleg oznake izbire."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These options are independent of each other. Pages that do not set a font "
"size, or ask for the default, will display with the size you set from "
"<guilabel>Medium font size</guilabel>, while any pages that ask for a size "
"smaller than your <guilabel>Minimum font size</guilabel> setting will "
"instead show that size. The one does not affect the other."
msgstr ""
"Te možnosti so neodvisne druga od druge. Strani, ki ne nastavijo velikosti "
"pisave ali zahtevajo privzeto, bodo prikazane z velikostjo, ki ste jo "
"nastavili v <guilabel>Srednji velikosti pisave</guilabel>, medtem ko vse "
"strani, ki zahtevajo velikost, manjšo od vaše <guilabel>Minimalne velikosti "
"pisave velikost</guilabel> namesto tega prikaže to velikost. Eno ne vpliva "
"na drugo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The remaining options are for the fonts to be associated with different "
"types of markup used in &HTML; pages. Note that many web pages may override "
"these settings. For any type of font (Standard, Fixed, Serif, &etc;) you can "
"select a different font if you like."
msgstr ""
"Preostale možnosti so, da se pisave povežejo z različnimi vrstami oznak, ki "
"se uporabljajo v &HTML; strani. Upoštevajte, da lahko številne spletne "
"strani preglasijo te nastavitve. Za katero koli vrsto pisave (standardno, "
"fiksno, serif, &etc;) lahko izberete drugo pisavo, če želite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below this, you can set a <guilabel>Font size adjustment for this encoding</"
"guilabel>. Sometimes the fonts you want to use for a particular encoding or "
"language are much larger or smaller than average, so you can use this "
"setting to bring them into line."
msgstr ""
"Pod tem lahko nastavite <guilabel>Prilagoditve velikosti pisave za to "
"kodiranje</guilabel>. Včasih so namreč pisave, ki bi jih radi uporabljali za "
"določeno kodiranje ali jezik, prevelike ali premajhne glede na običajne, "
"zato lahko uporabite to nastavitev in jih uskladite z drugimi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can set a default encoding that &konqueror; should assume pages are when "
"rendering them. The default setting is <guilabel>Use Language Encoding</"
"guilabel>, but you can change it to any encoding available in the list."
msgstr ""
"Nastavite lahko privzeto kodiranje, ki ga &konqueror; bi morali domnevati, "
"da so strani pri upodabljanju. Privzeta nastavitev je <guilabel>Uporabi "
"jezikovno kodiranje</guilabel>, vendar jo lahko spremenite v katero koli "
"kodiranje, ki je na voljo na seznamu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:144 index.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Stylesheets</title>"
msgstr "<title>Slogovnice</title>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>CSS</acronym> style sheets affect the way web pages appear. "
"<acronym>CSS</acronym> stands for <emphasis>C</emphasis>ascading "
"<emphasis>S</emphasis>tyle <emphasis>S</emphasis>heets."
msgstr ""
"Slogovne tabele <acronym>CSS</acronym> vplivajo na to, kako se spletne "
"strani prikazujejo. <acronym>CSS</acronym> pomeni <emphasis>K</"
"emphasis>askadne <emphasis>S</emphasis>log <emphasis>S</emphasis>logovnice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&konqueror; can use its own stylesheet, based on simple defaults and the "
"color scheme you are using for your desktop. &konqueror; can also use a "
"stylesheet that you have written yourself. Finally, you can specify a "
"stylesheet in this module. The options presented in this module are tuned "
"for accessibility purposes, especially for people with reduced vision."
msgstr ""
"&konqueror; lahko uporablja lastno slogovno tabelo, ki temelji na preprostih "
"privzetih nastavitvah in barvni shemi, ki jo uporabljate za namizje. "
"&konqueror; lahko uporabi tudi slogovno datoteko, ki ste jo napisali sami. "
"Končno lahko v tem modulu določite slogovno datoteko. Možnosti predstavljene "
"v tem modulu, so prilagojene za namene dostopnosti, zlasti za ljudi z "
"zmanjšanim vidom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Your choices here affect every &kde; application that renders HTML with "
"&kde;’s own renderer, which is called khtml. These include &kmail;, "
"&khelpcenter; and of course &konqueror;. Choices here do not affect other "
"browsers such as &firefox;."
msgstr ""
"Vaše izbire tukaj vplivajo na vsako &kde; aplikacijo, ki upodablja HTML z "
"lastnim upodobilnikom &kde;, ki se imenuje khtml. Te vključujejo &kmail;, "
"&khelpcenter; in seveda &konqueror;. Izbire tukaj ne vplivajo na druge "
"brskalnike, kot je &firefox;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section contains the following options:"
msgstr "Ta razdelek vsebuje naslednje možnosti:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use default stylesheet"
msgstr "Uporabi privzeto slogovno predlogo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kde; will use the default stylesheet. Some of the colors will default to "
"those defined in your chosen color scheme. Most settings are easily "
"overridden by the page you are viewing."
msgstr ""
"&kde; bo uporabil privzeto slogovno predlogo. Nekatere izmed barv bodo imele "
"privzete vrednosti, ki so definirane v vaši barvni shemi. Večino nastavitev "
"zlahka povozijo same spletne strani, ki si jih ogledujete."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use user-defined stylesheet"
msgstr "Uporabi uporabniško določene slogovne predloge"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kde; will use a stylesheet that you have written yourself. You can use the "
"browse button to locate the stylesheet on your system. <acronym>CSS</"
"acronym> files traditionally have a <literal role=\"extension\">.css</"
"literal> extension, but this is not required."
msgstr ""
"&kde; bo uporabil slogovno tabelo, ki ste jo napisali sami. Z gumbom za "
"brskanje lahko poiščete slogovno datoteko v vašem sistemu. Datoteke "
"<acronym>CSS</acronym> imajo običajno pripono <literal role=\"extension\">."
"css</literal>, vendar ta ni obvezna."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use accessibility stylesheet"
msgstr "Uporabite slogovno datoteko dostopnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the settings defined in the <guilabel>Customize</guilabel> dialog. "
"Enabling this option will enable the <guibutton>Customize</guibutton> button "
"lo launch a dialog to define stylesheet settings."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite nastavitve, določene v pogovornem oknu <guilabel>Prilagodi</"
"guilabel>. Če omogočite to možnost, boste omogočili gumb "
"<guibutton>Prilagodi</guibutton> za odpiranje pogovornega okna za določitev "
"nastavitev slogovne datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customize"
msgstr "Prilagoditi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this dialog you can set up a user stylesheet. The options available are "
"only a subset of the instructions you can add in a stylesheet, and they are "
"geared towards people with reduced vision, to allow users to create a "
"stylesheet that makes web pages and the &kde; help files more readable."
msgstr ""
"V tem pogovornem oknu lahko nastavite uporabniško tabelo slogov. Možnosti, "
"ki so na voljo, so samo podnabor navodil, ki jih lahko dodate v slogovno "
"datoteko, in so namenjene ljudem z zmanjšanim vidom, da uporabnikom "
"omogočijo ustvarjanje slogovne tabele, s katero spletne strani in &kde; "
"datoteke pomoči bolj berljive."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The options in this dialog are disabled unless you chose <guilabel>Use "
"accessibility stylesheet</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Možnosti v tem pogovornem oknu so onemogočene, razen če izberete "
"<guilabel>Uporabi slogovno tabelo dostopnosti</guilabel>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid "Font Family"
msgstr "Družina pisav"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Base family"
msgstr "Osnovna družina"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose a font family to use for body text."
msgstr "Izberite družino pisav za uporabo v telesu besedila."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use same family for all text"
msgstr "Za vse besedilo uporabi isto družino"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you enable this, then the same font family will be used for all text, "
"regardless of the settings on the page you are viewing. This is useful for "
"pages which have used a decorative or hard to read font for headlines."
msgstr ""
"Če omogočite to, bo za vse besedilo uporabljana ista družina pisav, ne glede "
"na nastavitve strani, ki jo gledate. To je uporabno pri straneh, ki za "
"naslove uporabljajo okrasne ali težko berljive pisave."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Font Size"
msgstr "Velikost pisave"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "Base font size"
msgstr "Osnovna velikost pisave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the default size for text on the page. Many web sites set their font "
"sizes relative to this default, using <quote>larger</quote> or <quote>+1</"
"quote> to make the text bigger, and <quote>smaller</quote> or <quote>-1</"
"quote> to make the text smaller."
msgstr ""
"To je privzeta velikost besedila na strani. Mnoge spletne strani nastavijo "
"svoje velikosti pisav relativno glede na to privzeto vrednost, z uporabo "
"oznak <quote>večje</quote> ali <quote>+1</quote> za večje, oziroma "
"<quote>manjše</quote> ali <quote>-1</quote> za manjše besedilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many people design their web pages on platforms where the ordinary default "
"text size is too large for the average user to read, so it is very common to "
"come across web pages that have forced the font smaller in this way."
msgstr ""
"Mnogi ljudje načrtujejo svoje spletne strani na platformah, kjer je običajna "
"privzeta velikost besedila prevelika, da bi jo povprečni uporabnik lahko "
"bral, zato zelo pogosto naletimo na spletne strani, ki na ta način zahtevajo "
"manjšo pisavo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This setting will allow you to set the default font to a comfortable size, "
"so that the relative sizes are also enlarged enough to be comfortable."
msgstr ""
"Ta nastavitev vam bo omogočila, da nastavite privzeto pisavo na udobno "
"velikost, tako da bodo tudi relativne velikosti dovolj povečane, da bodo še "
"berljive."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not forget you can also have &konqueror; enforce a minimum size, so that "
"text is <emphasis>never</emphasis> too small to read."
msgstr ""
"Ne pozabite, da imate lahko tudi &konqueror; uveljavi najmanjšo velikost, "
"tako da besedilo <emphasis>nikoli</emphasis> ni premajhno za branje."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use same size for all elements"
msgstr "Za vse elemente uporabi isto velikost"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you enable this option, then all text will be rendered at your specified "
"font size, regardless of the instructions the page contains. Relative font "
"sizes as discussed earlier, and even specific instructions that text should "
"be rendered at a certain size will be overridden here."
msgstr ""
"Če omogočite to izbiro, bo vse besedilo upodobljeno na vaši določeni "
"velikosti pisave, ne glede na navodila, ki jih vsebuje stran. Relativne "
"velikosti pisav, ki smo jih omenjali prej, in celo posebna navodila, da naj "
"bo pisava točno določene velikosti, bodo s tem prezrta."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Images"
msgstr "Slike"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suppress images"
msgstr "Prezri slike"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you do not want to view images, you can turn this off here."
msgstr "Če si ne želite ogledati slik, lahko to izklopite tukaj."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:287
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suppress background images"
msgstr "Prezri slike v ozadju"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One major problem for reduced vision users is that background images do not "
"give sufficient contrast to allow them to read the text. You can disable "
"background images here, independently of your choice above to view all "
"images."
msgstr ""
"Ena glavnih težav za slabovidne uporabnike je, da slike v ozadju ne dajejo "
"dovolj kontrasta, da bi lahko brali besedilo. Tukaj lahko onemogočite slike "
"ozadja, ne glede na vašo zgornjo izbiro, da si ogledate vse slike."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Colors"
msgstr "Barve"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:303
#, no-c-format
msgid "Black on white"
msgstr "Črno na belem"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many people with reduced vision find black text on a white screen gives the "
"most contrast, and is easiest to read. If this applies to you, you can set "
"this here."
msgstr ""
"Mnogim slabovidnim ljudem se zdi, da je črno besedilo na beli podlagi "
"najbolj kontrastno in zato najberljivejše. Če to velja tudi za vas, lahko to "
"nastavite tukaj."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "White on black"
msgstr "Belo na črnem"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many other people with reduced vision find the opposite to be true, that "
"white text on a black screen is easier to read."
msgstr ""
"Mnogim drugim slabovidnim ljudem se zdi ravno obratno, da je torej "
"berljivejše belo besedilo na črni podlagi."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:320
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom"
msgstr "Po meri"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Still other people find that pure black and white, in either order, is "
"difficult to read. You can set custom colors here for both the "
"<guilabel>Background</guilabel> and the <guilabel>Foreground</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Nekaterim drugim ljudem pa se kljub temu zdi, da sta čista črna in bela, v "
"kateremkoli vrstnem redu, težko berljivi. Tu lahko nastavite prilagojene "
"barve za <guilabel>Ozadje</guilabel> in <guilabel>Ospredje</guilabel>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use same color for all text"
msgstr "Za vse besedilo uporabi isto barvo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many web sites use a different, often contrasting color for headings or "
"other flourishes. If this interferes with your ability to read the content, "
"you can enable this check box to have &kde; use the colors you have set "
"above for all text."
msgstr ""
"Številna spletna mesta uporabljajo drugačne, pogosto kontrastne barve za "
"naslove ali druge dodatke. Če to ovira vašo zmožnost branja vsebine, lahko "
"omogočite to potrditveno polje, da bo &kde; uporabite barve, ki ste jih "
"nastavili zgoraj za celotno besedilo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:343
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preview"
msgstr "Predogled"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Preview</guilabel> section allows you to see the effect of "
"your changes. Several types of headings are displayed with your stylesheet, "
"and a sentence in the default body text."
msgstr ""
"Razdelek <guilabel>Predogled</guilabel> vam omogoča, da vidite učinek svojih "
"sprememb. Več vrst naslovov je prikazanih z vašo datoteko slogov in stavek v "
"privzetem osrednjem besedilu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This should allow you to fine-tune your stylesheet until you have something "
"that you can comfortably read."
msgstr ""
"To bi vam moralo omogočiti natančno prilagajanje vaše slogovne tabele, "
"dokler ne dobite nekaj, kar lahko udobno berete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid "Happy surfing!"
msgstr "Veselo brskanje!"

